What you need to know:  Infantino was in the city of Santos, Brazil, to pay his final respects to the player widely considered the greatest of all time, who died Thursday at the age of 82Infantino was among the first to pay homage before Pele's open casket, which was displayed in the middle of the field at Vila Belmiro stadiumFifa had already flown the flags of the world at half-mast last Friday outside its headquarters in Zurich in honour of Pele, whom the organisation has named as the greatest player of the 20th century